Limbaugh strangely alludes to an important point.
The meaning of the statue depends on your point of view.
Emma Lazarus describes the sculpture from the perspective of an exhausted and doomed traveler who, after a long and often terrifying voyage across the ocean, arrives with hope in his heart in a new land.
It's literally about seeing the world through the eyes of people who are seeking refuge and a chance for a better life.
