Islamists have been given life sentences in Britain for plotting an attack.
A British court on Thursday jailed for life four members of an Islamist cell calling itself the Three Musketeers who prosecutors said were planning a terrorist attack against the police and army.
The four men, two of whom attended a training camp in Pakistan and had previous convictions for similar offences, were arrested last August.
Authorities at the time believed he was preparing an imminent attack.
In the car of one of the men, security agents found a partially constructed pipe bomb, knives with inscriptions that mean "unbeliever" in Arabic, and a replica pistol.
It happened when an MI5 agent planted a listening device in the car.
