Facebook plans more thorough fact-checking to curb fake news
Facebook will send more potentially false articles for third-party review and display the findings below the original posts in an effort to combat so-called "fake news", the largest social network said Thursday.
In a statement on its website, the company says it will begin using updated machine learning to detect possible hoaxes, which it will send to third parties for verification and potentially display survey results below original posts.
