In a further statement issued in Germany on Thursday, Facebook said it was preparing to launch a test of a new fake news check feature in the United States, France, the Netherlands and Germany.
"In addition to seeing third-party verified news, people are asking for more content to make informed choices about what to share", Sara Su, Facebook's news product manager, said in a blog post.
