According to the UN, Afghan democracy relies on women in politics.
Elections can only be credible if all members of society, including women, participate, the UN representative in Afghanistan said Wednesday.
Nicholas Haysom, the head of the UN Assistance Mission, said that hundreds of women are running in local elections, three women are running for vice president, and more than 30 percent of newly registered voters are women.
"The role of women cannot be ignored", he said in a statement on Wednesday.
Elections can only be fully representative and credible if women participate in them, as well as in all related electoral processes.
Local and presidential elections will be held in Afghanistan on 5 April.
The Taliban have issued several threats against the electoral process, which has put international fighting on the back burner.
In this year's election, for the first time ever, one democratically elected government peacefully transfers power to the next.
Haysom said the strong role of women would strengthen Afghanistan's democracy.
Afghanistan's Independent Election Commission said 1.2 million of the 3.6 million registered voters were women.
The one-of-a-kind brewery is making beer again.
Here's to good beer in a resurrected brewery.
The enthusiasm and honesty of the new owners brought the brewery back to life a few years ago.
The brewery, first mentioned in 1586, has a Renaissance core and was converted into a steam engine operation in the nineteenth century.
Years of prosperity followed, when the brewery was known mainly for its dark beers.
Unfortunately, production was stopped during World War II, and in 1984 the brewery was nationalized.
Since then, the buildings have served as a state farm.
The work of destruction was done by the owners of the brewery after 1989.
The abandoned compound was devastated and dismantled for building materials.
In 2007, however, new hope shone in the form of new owners, architects Jana and Pavel Prouzov.
They began repairing the buildings with the utmost respect for the spirit of the building and every detail.
They carefully studied and continue to study archival materials, trying to preserve the original materials and building elements.
The brewery thus looks much as it did in the 19th century, when its golden age began.
Their work was recognised when the Ministry of Culture declared the brewery a cultural monument and the building became part of the European Route of Industrial Heritage.
In 2015, the tradition of brewing beer was solemnly restored.
If you would like to taste the excellent Lobeč beer in the picturesque countryside of Kokořínsko, visit the tavern on the brewery grounds.
In brewing beer, they use kokořín water from a protected landscape area, malt from the Lobeč fields and hops.
The bar serves traditional pale lagers as well as dark beers and specials.
And don't miss the brewery tour, held Saturday and Sunday at noon and 1:30.
The largest artillery fortress in Czechoslovakia?
One of the largest fortresses of its kind in the world?
Such a unique structure was to be the Stachelberg fortress between Trutnov and Žacléř, on top of a ridge above the village of Babí.
Originally, it was to consist of up to twelve bunkers connected by an extensive underground passage.
This was to be the headquarters, barracks, ammunition and material stores, power station, engine room, and hospital.
However, the Munich Agreement halted construction.
In less than a year, a single massive reinforced-concrete bunker was built and underground passages were blasted open.
Thanks to the enthusiasts of the Stachelberg Association, who began restoring the unique building in the early 1990's, you too can visit it.
Access to the basement is now 75%!
In addition to the infantry hut T-S 73 with an exposition and underground, the complex also includes an armed light fortification facility, two under construction infantry huts, trenches and a nature trail Fortified Trutnovsko.
Refreshments, a cozy gazebo, and breathtaking views of the countryside are guaranteed!
This unique and beautiful Czech structure was listed alongside such monuments as the Great Wall of China, Trajan's Harbour near Rome, and the Assyrian palaces of Nineveh and Nimrud.
